title: Long Way Forward - Part 32
body:
Thank you for patiently waiting! 

gif is not mine

Mood swings and cravings

It’s been more than a month since the house party. You two haven’t used any protection since that night, but you didn’t want to stress about it. You were like ‘It comes when it comes.’ Both of you started working more. Harry needed to record his album so he was out for all days on Abbey Road, which wasn’t far from where you live. But still you were alone, so you started working too. You visited your favorite producer, Cam Blackwood to find dates to go to his studio to record your album. You also had another charity concert planned, but this time you started arranging it months before.

One morning you were lying in bed, Harry’s arm was somehow under you but in a comfortable way, you slept on it. But it wasn’t the first thing you felt when your eyes opened. Your stomach. It felt like it turned upside down. You quickly got out of bed and ran into the bathroom, because you felt something coming up. Harry woke up too when he felt the sudden movement and when he saw you running away he jumped out of bed after you.

You knelt down by the toilet but  nothing actually came out. You still felt bad though.

“Love, can I help? What’s the matter?”

“Leave me alone” you shouted. Harry was surprised by your kind of rude words. You looked up at him.

“Sorry. I feel like i ate something nasty”

“The sushi from last night? Do you think it was bad?”

“I don’t know. Ugh… I’m not sure I want breakfast” you stood up.

“You gotta eat something. Can I do anything?”

“No, thanks! I’ll be in the kitchen in five minutes” he left and you looked down at your growling belly.

“I’ll never eat sushi again…” you whispered to yourself. You got dressed and joined Harry in the kitchen. Now looking at food you realize you’re actually hungry. You buttered two slices of bread and then you put mayo on top. You drank coffee with it. Harry looked at your choice of breakfast and looked confused.

“You said you don’t want to eat and you eat mayo bread with coffee. Don’t you think this is gonna make you go to the bathroom?” he smiled at the end.

“Why are you so concerned?” you sounded annoyed.

“Sorry I asked.” Harry left a little later to work. You called Cam that you won’t go into the studio today. You called Sara after that.

“Hi, Sara!”

“Hi!”

“Look, I want to ask you something, but you can’t tell anyone”

“Okay”

“Can you go to the pharmacy for me?”

“What do you need?

“Pregnancy tests”

In an hour Sara knocked and you let her in.

“I didn’t know which one is better so I bought one from every brand.”

“Thanks! Now I’ll go and pee on each one of them”

“y/n, that’s six, I’m pretty sure three is enough”

“We’ll see.” You came out a few minutes later. You and Sara sat next to each other watching the timer.

“So you think you’re pregnant”

“I tried to ignore the signs, I felt sick and I have other symptoms. I just wanna know.”

“But you want a baby, don’t you?”

“Yes, we really want a baby, but it’s my first pregnancy I’m nervous and anxious”

“It’s exciting” she nudged your arm.

“Yeah, I just don’t know what to do or what not to do”

“You’re gonna be great parents. I know both of you well enough to know that” she smiled and actually made you feel better. You almost jumped as the alarm beeped. The time was up. You looked at Sara.

“Go, momma” she smiled. You walked back into the bathroom. The three tests were on the sink and you cautiously looked at them. You suddenly couldn’t breathe and cried ut for Sara. She rushed in.

“What?” she looked at the tests.

“Sara, are these really three positive tests?” you looked desperate. She laughed.

“Yes.”

“No.”

“Yes. They are. y/n! You’re gonna be a mum!” she shouted.

“How will you tell Harry?”

“I… I have no idea.” you heard your phone ring. It was Harry.

“Hi, babe! I just called to tell I’ll be home by 2.”

“That’s… that’s great! Good!”

“Are you alright?” he asked.

“Yes, of course. I’m fine. I’ll wait for you”

“Aren’t you in the studio?”

“No, I still feel sick.”

“Oh, then I’ll hurry to go home to cuddle you by the tv while caressing your belly”

“Thanks, love” you hung up.

“Sara, I have an idea. Take me to the nearest baby shop”

You went to a baby shop that was a few blocks away. You chose a pair of the smallest shoes that were neither pink or blue. It was beige. Sara took you back and you were too excited to start cooking so you opened your macbook and started reading about pregnancy, you got so lost in it that you haven’t realized how fast time passed. You heard Harry coming in. You suddenly looked up and hid the tiny shoes.

“Hello” he shouted from the hallway.

“I’m in the sitting room” you shouted back. You remained in your sitting position. He sat down next to you and kissed you.

“I’m so glad you’re not working, I don’t know what I would’ve done without you. I’d be sitting alone watching a romcom…”

“Harry” you couldn’t hold back your excitement.

“Yes.”

“I have a surprise for you”

“Mmm” he moaned softly.

“Close your eyes”

“Okay” he did close his eyes. “Are you gonna kiss me?”

“Probably, but first…” you grabbed his hand and turned it around so you could place the tiny shoes in his hand. He frowned.

“Can I open now?”

“Yeah” he opened his eyes and looked at his hands. He was holding the little baby shoes.

“Is it…?”

“Yes”

“Are you…?”

“Probably”

“I’m going to be?”

“I guess”  he hugged you tightly and you heard him crying. You pulled away and faced him. Now you were crying together. He kissed you.

“You’re gonna be a great mum and I’m so proud of you.”

You started talking about the first steps. You had to find the doctor to confirm the pregnancy, you needed to think about which room to renovate first for the baby. You agreed that you won’t tell anyone including family members that you’re pregnant until you’re at least 12 weeks pregnant. In the following days Harry was incredibly protective, he went to the pharmacy with you to buy vitamins and everything that you possibly needed. He bought some child safety stuff for the furnitures and plugs.

Next week you went to see the doctor. You were very excited just as Harry. The doctor confirmed you are about five weeks pregnant and told you all the things you needed to do to welcome the baby. These were days of joy and constant happiness that you’ve never felt before. You were married to your best friend and lover, you were carrying his child under your heart and your career was at its best. Life seemed beautiful and it was. You couldn’t wait to be 12 weeks pregnant and tell everyone the good news. Two weeks later you were looking at cute little baby clothes online and Harry was in the kitchen making tea. You felt your stomach ache a bit, but you brushed it off. Harry arrived with the teas and joined you in the hunting for little jumpsuits. A little later - as usual - you felt the need to pee after tea and your stomach hurt more, so you stood up to go to the bathroom. Harry gasped. You turned around to see him.

“Y/N” you never saw his face more upset. But the moment you looked back you knew why he gasped. The blanket you were sitting on was bloody in a big spot. Your heart rate rose and Harry automatically grabbed his phone to call 999.

“Yes. They are. y/n! You’re gonna be a mum!” she shouted.

“How will you tell Harry?”

“I… I have no idea.” you heard your phone ring. It was Harry.

“Hi, babe! I just called to tell I’ll be home by 2.”

“That’s… that’s great! Good!”

“Are you alright?” he asked.

“Yes, of course. I’m fine. I’ll wait for you”

“Aren’t you in the studio?”

“No, I still feel sick.”

“Oh, then I’ll hurry to go home to cuddle you by the tv while caressing your belly”

“Thanks, love” you hung up.

“Sara, I have an idea. Take me to the nearest baby shop”

You went to a baby shop that was a few blocks away. You chose a pair of the smallest shoes that were neither pink or blue. It was beige. Sara took you back and you were too excited to start cooking so you opened your macbook and started reading about pregnancy, you got so lost in it that you haven’t realized how fast time passed. You heard Harry coming in. You suddenly looked up and hid the tiny shoes.

“Hello” he shouted from the hallway.

“I’m in the sitting room” you shouted back. You remained in your sitting position. He sat down next to you and kissed you.

“I’m so glad you’re not working, I don’t know what I would’ve done without you. I’d be sitting alone watching a romcom…”

“Harry” you couldn’t hold back your excitement.

“Yes.”

“I have a surprise for you”

“Mmm” he moaned softly.

“Close your eyes”

“Okay” he did close his eyes. “Are you gonna kiss me?”

“Probably, but first…” you grabbed his hand and turned it around so you could place the tiny shoes in his hand. He frowned.

“Can I open now?”

“Yeah” he opened his eyes and looked at his hands. He was holding the little baby shoes.

“Is it…?”

“Yes”

“Are you…?”

“Probably”

“I’m going to be?”

“I guess”  he hugged you tightly and you heard him crying. You pulled away and faced him. Now you were crying together. He kissed you.

“You’re gonna be a great mum and I’m so proud of you.”

You started talking about the first steps. You had to find the doctor to confirm the pregnancy, you needed to think about which room to renovate first for the baby. You agreed that you won’t tell anyone including family members that you’re pregnant until you’re at least 12 weeks pregnant. In the following days Harry was incredibly protective, he went to the pharmacy with you to buy vitamins and everything that you possibly needed. He bought some child safety stuff for the furnitures and plugs.

Next week you went to see the doctor. You were very excited just as Harry. The doctor confirmed you are about five weeks pregnant and told you all the things you needed to do to welcome the baby. These were days of joy and constant happiness that you’ve never felt before. You were married to your best friend and lover, you were carrying his child under your heart and your career was at its best. Life seemed beautiful and it was. You couldn’t wait to be 12 weeks pregnant and tell everyone the good news. Two weeks later you were looking at cute little baby clothes online and Harry was in the kitchen making tea. You felt your stomach ache a bit, but you brushed it off. Harry arrived with the teas and joined you in the hunting for little jumpsuits. A little later - as usual - you felt the need to pee after tea and your stomach hurt more, so you stood up to go to the bathroom. Harry gasped. You turned around to see him.

“Y/N” you never saw his face more upset. But the moment you looked back you knew why he gasped. The blanket you were sitting on was bloody in a big spot. Your heart rate rose and Harry automatically grabbed his phone to call 999.

title: my blog in 2019
body:
Hey guys!

If you know my blog (its okay if you dont!) you probably know that its been a bit barren of late. I was veryyyy busy in 2018 studying hard, but I’m hoping this year I will have more time to write. 

I am, however, lacking inspiration and I was hoping you would help me out by sending blurb requests (for harry obvi). I might do themes, I might not, but I was hoping you guys could send me concepts and I could do little blurbs for them to get back in the swing of things. 

My goal is also to finish the fics I started but never finished! I promise I haven’t forgotten!

(I know I’ve said this before, don’t judge me lol)

Here is my other writing for reference!

Have a happy new year guys, I’m hoping to hear a lot more from you this year and give you some writings about the boy we all love!

Lots of love xx
